-- Carmelo Anthony Sprains Ankle as Grizzlies Snap Knicks’ Unbeaten NBA Run
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-01-13T05:00:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/carmelo-anthony-sprains-ankle-as-grizzlies-snap-knicks-unbeaten-nba-run.html
The  New York Knicks ’ four-game
winning streak ended with a 94-83 defeat at the  Memphis
Grizzlies  in which the Knicks lost leading scorer Carmelo Anthony to a sprained right ankle.  Rudy Gay scored 26 points for the Grizzlies in the National
Basketball Association game last night at FedExForum in Memphis.
O.J. Mayo came off the bench to add 18 points for the Grizzlies.  Anthony, who leads the Knicks with an average of 26 points
per game, left the game in the third quarter and did not return.
Anthony and reserve Bill Walker each scored 14 points to lead
the Knicks.  The Knicks (6-5) are second in the Eastern Conference’s
five-team Atlantic Division, 1 1/2 games behind the  Philadelphia
76ers . The Grizzlies (4-6) are third in the Western Conference’s
Southwest Division, 2 1/2 games behind the San Antonio Spurs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
